  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Getting Started&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Begin by defining&amp;nbsp;the appropriate approach for training and user support (e.g. web-based training, classroom&#xD;
    instruction, mentoring). The approach is based on the organization's&amp;nbsp;business goals and job/&amp;nbsp;task performance&#xD;
    requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Next,&amp;nbsp;draft a plan for developing the education and support materials. This plan will be refined throughout the&#xD;
    project lifecycle. Include a description of the deliverables and the&amp;nbsp;required roles and responsibilities for their&#xD;
    development.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is important to pilot the training and support&amp;nbsp;materials in order to gain feedback on their effectiveness.&#xD;
    Adjust as needed prior to full deployment. The actual rollout of training will need to be tailored based on the type of&#xD;
    training being conducted. In this practice,&amp;nbsp;the tasks assume a classroom-based approach utilizing a Train the&#xD;
    Trainer&amp;nbsp;method to bring additional instructors up to speed.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
